        {
          "node_id": "tutorial/header-param-models::section-0004",
          "parent_id": "tutorial/header-param-models::section-0001",
          "level": 2,
          "node_kind": "heading",
          "heading_text": "Forbid Extra Headers",
          "anchor_id": "forbid-extra-headers",
          "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/header-param-models/#forbid-extra-headers",
          "section_text_parts": [
            "In some special use cases (probably not very common), you might want to restrict the headers that you want to receive.",
            "You can use Pydantic's model configuration to forbid any extra fields:",
            "If a client tries to send some extra headers , they will receive an error response.",
            "For example, if the client tries to send a tool header with a value of plumbus , they will receive an error response telling them that the header parameter tool is not allowed:"
          ],
          "section_text": "In some special use cases (probably not very common), you might want to restrict the headers that you want to receive.\n\nYou can use Pydantic's model configuration to forbid any extra fields:\n\nIf a client tries to send some extra headers , they will receive an error response.\n\nFor example, if the client tries to send a tool header with a value of plumbus , they will receive an error response telling them that the header parameter tool is not allowed:",
          "section_inline_code": [
            "forbid",
            "extra",
            "tool",
            "plumbus"
          ],
          "section_links": [],
          "code_refs": [
            {
              "type": "code_ref",
              "path": "../../docs_src/header_param_models/tutorial002_an_py310.py",
              "highlight_lines": [
                10
              ],
              "raw": "{* ../../docs_src/header_param_models/tutorial002_an_py310.py hl[10] *}",
              "section_id": "tutorial/header-param-models::section-0004",
              "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/header-param-models/#forbid-extra-headers"
            }
          ],
          "code_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "code_block",
              "language": "json",
              "text": "{\n    \"detail\": [\n        {\n            \"type\": \"extra_forbidden\",\n            \"loc\": [\"header\", \"tool\"],\n            \"msg\": \"Extra inputs are not permitted\",\n            \"input\": \"plumbus\",\n        }\n    ]\n}",
              "section_id": "tutorial/header-param-models::section-0004",
              "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/header-param-models/#forbid-extra-headers"
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "node_id": "tutorial/header-param-models::section-0005",
          "parent_id": "tutorial/header-param-models::section-0001",
          "level": 2,
          "node_kind": "heading",
          "heading_text": "Disable Convert Underscores",
          "anchor_id": "disable-convert-underscores",
          "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/header-param-models/#disable-convert-underscores",
          "section_text_parts": [
            "The same way as with regular header parameters, when you have underscore characters in the parameter names, they are automatically converted to hyphens .",
            "For example, if you have a header parameter save_data in the code, the expected HTTP header will be save-data , and it will show up like that in the docs.",
            "If for some reason you need to disable this automatic conversion, you can do it as well for Pydantic models for header parameters."
          ],
          "section_text": "The same way as with regular header parameters, when you have underscore characters in the parameter names, they are automatically converted to hyphens .\n\nFor example, if you have a header parameter save_data in the code, the expected HTTP header will be save-data , and it will show up like that in the docs.\n\nIf for some reason you need to disable this automatic conversion, you can do it as well for Pydantic models for header parameters.",
          "section_inline_code": [
            "save_data",
